data.text:
Cyprus first participated at the Olympic Games in 1980. This nation has participated in every Winter Olympic Games since Lake Placid 1980.

Cyprus has won one medal at the Olympic Games, a silver medal won in 2012.

The Cyprus Olympic Committee was created in 1974 and recognized in 1978.
